{
  "texts": [
    "The factory layout can be rearranged, whenever a new scheduling decision is requested.",
    "For the target position of a station, only coordinates that do not lie on blocked space, e.g., unmovable stations, are considered.",
    "A boundary is added to blocked spaces corresponding to the half the size of the station that must get moved to avoid overlapping stations.",
    "Hence, it is avoided that objects overlap when the centroid of the station gets moved to the available coordinate.",
    "A visualization of the reconfiguration procedure is shown in Fig. 5."
  ]
}